Text.Value: Fortunately for you, I have grander game than you to stalk.
I wager the rats here are really scary.
Focus. Dedication. Utmost vigilance.
You may run with your tail between your legs, but I fear no man nor beast - particularly cowards who hide behind magic. Bah.
What is wrong with me?! Gods help me.
I braved lapping waters and leaking ships to find this prey. I butchered many, and will butcher many more.

EditorData.NodeContext: cold and murderous but starting to get a little excited at the mention of the butchering

Text.Value: *Hiss.*
'Tadpole' the furless ones call them. But the name matters not, merely their demise.

EditorData.NodeContext: disinterested in the details, all she wants is to murder them. Cold and deadly tone.

Text.Value: Don't risk delving into the past's horrors. Ask about the tadpole.
*A memory won at the cost of a piece of mind: you were in this tower before. That much is sure.*
You clearly have delusions of grandeur.
Murder every single one you find.
Ah ha ha HA!
*The pleasure of the memory dribbles out of your leaking skull, into the very air...*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Dark urge snaps back to reality. The body of the cat is dead in front of them.

Text.Value: Leave.
Good luck with the hunt, Steelclaw.
Meow!
The tower isn't a safe place right now, maybe you should leave.
I am no kitten. I seek something far more challenging.
You skulked like you owned the place, trespassing on my domain.
Yours is a face I shred in my dreams.
What do you mean I kicked you? We've never met.
You're a little bit intense.
Lies, it merely pretends. But I am a patient hunter - I will wait for it to stir, and then I will strike.
*The cat pays you little attention, so focused is it on the hunt.*
How boring, surely you can be a bit more creative?
Those parasites are dangerous - they've harmed me sorely.
Sorry, your name is 'Steelclaw'?
I intend to.

EditorData.NodeContext: cold and murderous, she'll kill anything in her path

Text.Value: The parasites are dangerous, don't go near them.
*The message is clear - stay, if you wish, but she will flee at a moment's notice.*
Another will come soon, I have no doubt. So be silent - and do not interfere.
Cower in self-disgust.
You clearly yearn for death - a wish I am happy to oblige. Sleep with one eye open, furless one.
What type of prey are you waiting for?
Get out of here, stupid cat.
That parasite was mine. Spend your days in fear, furless one, for I will return to dig my claws into your eyes and rip out your brains!

EditorData.NodeContext: full on murderous psychopath here, she means every word

Text.Value: You're quite the hunter, aren't you?
*How the kitty-cat mewled when your boot stamped upon its tail! You are the black cat crossing the path of the living.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Dark urge starts to relish in the memory, but thinking about the memory brings it into reality. The dark urge blacks out using the DARK URGE RAGE template, and by the time the template goes, the cat is dead on the ground in front of them.

Text.Value: 'Slithering vermin'? They're called tadpoles.
*The cat huffs - unimpressed. She will do as she pleases.*
Ghost dragon, harbinger of death, child of the end. The tower feared you so, but one day I shall pry you apart scale by scale.
My past evils are lost to me. Now, I admire your hunt.
Hold out your hand, letting the cat sniff it.
Luck is not needed - merely patience and a thirst for blood. Hunt fast and hunt well.
*The cat ignores you, but her eyes stray to a small tunnel hidden in the wall.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: camera focuses at the small tunnel hidden in the wall

Text.Value: Do not mock me, braggart. Not every murderer has opposable thumbs. We cannot all create, I can only destroy.
But this one - this one I toy with. I slice, I tear, and when the time is right, I will bite its head off and bathe in its innards.

EditorData.NodeContext: going full on murderous psychopath as her excitement builds, peaking in the last line.

Text.Value: You simply do not understand the hunt. True joy is the feel of screaming flesh beneath your fangs.

EditorData.NodeContext: cats can't smirk,  but if they could she would be doing a hannibal smile as she described this

Text.Value: A fellow hunter is a welcome sight. Any tips on hunting tadpoles?
You know that tadpole is dead, right?
Your mocking tone is a mistake, your first and last.
*You excavate the empty caverns of your useless mind. Shovelling, dozing, blasting through the smoothbrain.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Dark urge closes eyes and winces trying to remember.

Text.Value: Do not push your own cowardice upon me.

EditorData.NodeContext: disgusted with the player. She is a hunter, she will kill only the most deadly of prey

Text.Value: I remove the vitals, turn the skin inside out, then stuff them.
*... murder, glorious murder.*
It is a name I earned through bloodshed and death. Unfortunately, the more ignorant here refuse to use it.
This place is dangerous, you should probably leave.
One who kicked the Steelclaw, as if I were some stray. I am a champion hunter. When I lick my pelt: I taste blood.
Try to remember what was forgotten.
The death-walker passed through here before. I know your scent. All were silent afore you, but I dared to snarl.
A fellow hunter is a welcome sight. What is your quarry?
These are the stalking grounds of Steelclaw, furless one - tread lightly.
I await the arrival of my next kill.
I will split and burst their every skin.
*The cat gazes at you with clear disinterest.*
Quiet, lest I miss its cries for mercy.

EditorData.NodeContext: wants the player to stop bothering her, cold and commanding

Text.Value: *The cat glares at you with utter hatred - you took the tadpole, its prey, and it will remember this slight.*
*The feline eyes the parasite with a glint in her eye, intent clear...*
I bet the rats here give you plenty of trouble.
'Fluffers' they call me. Idiots.
Fortunately for you, the slithering vermin I hunt has my attention - for now.

EditorData.NodeContext: cold and murderous, hinting that she'd turn on the player in an instant

Text.Value: *Purr.*

EditorData.SFXTags: [WI] Cat's purring sounds for it is happy

Text.Value: Now, I must return to my prey. It  has been too long since it felt the bite of fear.
Their name matters not, merely their demise.

Synopsis: As the player explore the surrounding of Moonrise, they can encounter a cat playing with a dead tadpole. Upon interacting with this cat, player can learn where the tadpoles are actually being stored at (SWA) or the location of a nearby tunnel they can use in cat form (Non-SWA). Steelclaw is a murdering psychopath who revels in blood and gore.
